OL,3,CBrooch given to first passenger to
OL,4,Cboard doomed steamship found at
OL,5,Croadshow
OL,7,FA brooch given to the first passenger
OL,8,Fto board a Dundee-built steamship 37
OL,9,Fyears before she sank has surfaced at
OL,10,Fan antiques roadshow.
OL,12,FThe decorative item was presented to
OL,13,FElizabeth Anderson on April 21 1894,
OL,14,Fthe date of the maiden voyage of the
OL,15,FSS Citrine.
OL,17,FBuilt by Dundee shipbuilders W B
OL,18,FThompson & Co, the Citrine was one of
OL,19,Fa number of vessels in the Glasgow-
OL,20,Fbased "Gem line", all of which were
OL,21,Fnamed after gemstones or minerals.
OL,26,@|D@GOU|D@PO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/7
