OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1782703089
OL,3,CBrooch given to first passenger to
OL,4,Cboard doomed steamship found at
OL,5,Croadshow
OL,7,FThe sides of the gold-coloured item
OL,8,Fare shaped as a ship's rope and its
OL,9,Fcentre has been designed as a life
OL,10,Fring mounted with a citrine stone,
OL,11,Fechoing the name of the vessel.
OL,13,FThe Citrine sank on March 17 1931
OL,14,Fafter striking rocks at Bradda Head,
OL,15,FPort Erin, on the Isle of Man.
OL,17,FAccounts at the time described the
OL,18,Fship's final moments in darkness,
OL,19,Fheavy weather and confusion, and the
OL,20,Fdisaster claimed the lives of nine of
OL,21,Fher 11 crew members.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
